===Usage Notes===
''Tāwai'' and ''tāwan'' (which decline the same as [[dēiws]]), the [[feminine]] and [[neuter]] forms of ''tāws'' (''father'', which by definition refers to a male), respectively, are grammatically possible but never used except as insults.

===Etymology===
===Noun===
'''tāws''' {{m}}
# [[father]] (see also [[tāwas]])

